<DOC><DOCNO> AP880909-0184 </DOCNO><FILEID>AP-NR-09-09-88 0734EDT</FILEID><FIRST>r w AM-House-Fires     09-09 0141</FIRST><SECOND>AM-House-Fires,1st Ld-Writethru,a0835,100</SECOND><HEAD>Congress Approves U.S.-Canadian Firefighting Mission</HEAD><NOTE>EDs:SUBS 1st graf include full congressional approval and CORRECTday from Wednesday to Thursday. Pickup 2nd graf pvs bgng ``Thelegislation...</NOTE><DATELINE>WASHINGTON (AP) </DATELINE><TEXT>   Congress adopted on Thursday a bill that wouldallow the U.S. government to contract with Canada to use thatcountry's firefighting resources to battle Western forest fires.   The legislation would allow the U.S. Forrest Service toreimburse Canada, thereby allowing that nation to send firemen,aircraft and other equipment. House Agriculture Committee stafferssaid Canada has 35 planes ready and available.   The U.S. government does not currently have the authority tocompensate the Canadians.   ``The devastating forest fires we're seeing throughout theNorthwest are causing a devastating impact on the firefightingcapabilities of the U.S. government,'' said Rep. Kika de la Garza,D-Texas, chairman of the Agriculture Committee.</TEXT></DOC>